FBIS3-6664 "dreas054_c_94017" FBIS-EAS-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Mar 1994 North Korea Kim Chong-il Replies to Foreign Party Leaders SK1803125694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1045 GMT 18 Mar 94 SK1803125694 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [All names as received] [Text] Pyongyang, March 18 (KCNA) -- The dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il sent messages to foreign party leaders in reply to their messages of greetings on the occasion of his birthday. Among them are Chea Sim, chairman of the Central Committee of the People's Party of Cambodia and speaker of the parliament of the Kingdom of Cambodia; Madhav Kumar Nepal, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist Party (United Marxism-Leninism); Narayan Man Bijukchhe, chairman of the Nepal Workers and Peasants Party; Samboram Shrestha, secretary general of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist League; Walid Joumblatt, president of the Socialist Progressive Party of Lebanon; Chairman Inaam Raad and General Secretary of the Supreme Council Ali Hassan of the Nationalist Socialist Party of Syria in Lebanon; Farouk Dahrouj, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Lebanese Communist Party; Abdallah al Chahal, secretary of the Lebanese Regional Leadership of the Arab Socialist Baath Party; Budragchagiyn Dashyondon, general secretary of the Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party; Dogu Ferincek, chairman of the Workers' Party of Turkey; Rafiq Ahmad Sheikh, secretary general of the Pakistan People's Party; C.R. Aslam, president of the Pakistan Socialist Party; Iqbal Ahmed Khan, secretary general of the Pakistan Muslim League; Vassos Lyssarides, chairman of the Socialist Party of Cyprus; Yacob Zayadine, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Jordanian Communist Party; Talal Hafun Ala Mai, general secretary of the People's Unity Party (Unionist) of Jordan; Indrajit Gupta, general secretary of the National Council of the Communist Party of India; Youssef Amin Wali, general secretary of the Egyptian National Democratic Party; Milud al Mahdabi, general secretary of the Permanent Secretariat of the Organization of Socialists in the Mediterranean; Roland Atta-Kesson, national chairman of the National Convention Party of Ghana; Huudu Yahaya, general secretary of the National Democratic Congress of Ghana; I.B.A. Kelepha Samba, national president of the People's Progressive Party of Gambia; El Hadj Boubacar Diallo, general secretary of the Party for Unity and Progress of Guinea; Ngirumpatse Mathieu, president of the National Republican Movement for the Democracy and Development of Rwanda; Mamadou El Bechir Gologo, secretary general of the National Direction Committee of the Sudanese Union-African Democratic Rally in Mali; Mohamedoun Dicko, secretary general of the Executive Committee of the African Party for the Solidarity and Justice of Mali; Nicolas Mayugi, chairman of the Central Committee of the Burundi Party of Unity for National Progress; Toe De Stanislas, general secretary of the Democratic Youth Revolutionary Party of Burkina Faso; Ali Houdou, secretary general of the Party of Revolution of Benin; Leonel Mario Da Alva, chairman of the Democratic Convergence Party and Reflexion Group of Sao Tome and Principe; Carlos Dias Da Graca, general secretary of the Liberation Movement-Social Democratic Party of Sao Tome and Principe; Emile Kibala Bey A Nsien, national chairman of the Workers' Party of Zaire; Otete Gaston Mboyo, national chairman of the National Movement of the Genuine Lumumbist Combatants of Zaire; Lambert Mende Omalanga, national chairman of the Lumumba Congolese National Movement-Original of Zaire; Gerand Francois Yandza, chairman of the African Socialist Movement of the Congo; Leon Nzokene, general secretary of the Congolese Socialist Party; Kamba Raymond, general secretary of the Congolese Communist Party; Amoussouvi Vignik Amedegnato, general secretary of the Togolese People's Rally; Mohamed Bel Hadj Amor, general secretary of the People's Unity Party of Tunisia; Khaled Bensmain, general secretary of the Movement for Democracy in Algeria; Eriya Kategaya, national political commissar of the National Resistance Movement of Uganda; Liewelyn John, leader of the People's Democratic Movement of Guyana; Peter Persaud, leader of the Amerindian Action Movement of Guyana; Terence A. Marryshow, political leader of the Maurice Bishop Patriotic Movement of Grenada; Daniel Ortega Saavedra, secretary general of the Sandinist National Liberation Front of Nicaragua; Rosie Douglas, leader of the Labour Party of Dominica; Miguel Mejia, secretary general of the Central Committee of the United Left Movement of Dominica; Sam Marcy, chairman of the Workers World Party of the United States; Gus Hall, national chairman of the Communist Party of the United States of America; George Belle, secretary general of the Barbados Workers' Party; Jorge Ibanez Castro, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Bolivian Communist Party; Joao Amazonas, chairman of the Central Committee of the Brazilian Communist Party; chairman Argelia Raya and international secretary Jorge Valero of the Venezuelan Movement to Socialism; Adelso Gonzalez Urdaneta, general secretary of the People's Electoral Movement of Venezuela; President Radames Larazabal and General Secretary Manuel Urbina of the Patriotic Federation of Venezuela; Orlando Van Amson, chairman of the National Democratic Party of Suriname; Vincent Cabrea, acting leader of the February 18th Movement of Trinidad and Tobago; Humberto Vargas Carbonel, secretary general of the Central Committee of the People's Vanguard of Costa Rica; Eduardo Mora Valverde, coordinator of the Central Committee of the People's Party of Costa Rica; Chairman Aida Abella Esquivel and International Secretary Julio Cesar Pachon of the National Leadership of the Patriotic Union of Colombia; Chairman Victor Sanchez Bilagra and General Secretary Ricardo Esti Garribia of the February Revolutionary Party of Paraguay; Andres Regiardo Sayan, national general secretary of the "Cambio 90" Movement of Peru; General Secretary Rena Raffo Munoz and International Secretary Guillermo Herrera Montecinos of the Central Committee of the Peruvian Communist Party; General Secretary Guzman Rivera Castaneda and International Secretary Luis Flores of the Socialist Revolutionary Party of Peru; Genaro Ledesma Izquieta, chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru; Javier Diaz Canseco, general secretary of the Mariateguista United Party of Peru; Gustavo Mohme Ryona, national secretary general of the Socialist Political Action Party of Peru; Luis Mateo Munos, general secretary of the Socialist Party of Peru; Angel Castro Lavarello, president of the National Executive Committee of the Left Revolutionary Union of Peru and concurrently chairman of the National Executive Committee of the Peruvian Front for National Liberation; Oscar Ugarte Ubilluz, national coordinator of the Left Democratic Movement of Peru; General Secretary Armando Villa Nueva and Deputy General Secretary Carlos Roca of the National Executive Committee of the American Popular Revolutionary Alliance of Peru; Denzil Douglas, leader of the Labour Party of St. Kitts-Nevis; Rigoberto Padilla Ruz, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Honduras; executive general secretaries Marina Arismendi, Carlos Tutzo, Pedro Balbi and executive member and International Secretary Roberto Catenachio of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Uruguay; Victor Granda Aguilar, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Socialist Party of Ecuador; General Secretry Peter Symon and President Hanna Elina Middleton of the Central Committee of the Socialist Party of Australia; Preben Moller Hansen, chairman of the Danish Workers' Party, common cause; Betty Frydensbjerg Carlsson, chairwoman of the Communist Party of Denmark; Klaus Riis, chairman of the Central Committee of the Communist Party (M-L) of Denmark; Vassalo Anthony, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Malta; Ludo Martens, chairman of the Central Committee of the Belgian Labour Party; Rolf Hagel, chairman of the Workers' Party-Communists of Sweden; Frank Baude, chairman of the Communist Party-KPML (R) of Sweden; Chairman Timo Lahdenmaki and General Secretary Heikki Mannikko of the for Peace and Socialism-the Communist Workers' Party of Finland; Blasco Hugo Fernandes, chairman of the National Direction Committee of the Democratic Intervention of Portugal; Manuel Vargas Loureiro, chairman of the Democratic Renovation Party of Portugal; President Marian Donnelly and General Secretary Pat Quearney of the Workers' Party of Ireland; General Secretary James Stewart and International Secretary Eoin O'murku of the National Executive Committee of the Communist Party of Ireland; Eric Trevett, general secretary of the Central Committee of the New Communist Party of Great Britain; Roberto Gabriele, general secretary of the Movement for Peace and Socialism of Italy; and David Baz, ex-chairman of the Nationalist Socialist Party of Syria in Lebanon. Comrade Kim Chong-il also sent reply messages to Shuachi Inoue, director general of the International Institute of the Chuche Idea [IIJI], and vice-directors general of the IIJI T.B. Mukherjee, president of the Asian Regional Institute of the Chuche Idea, Dorank Assifat Diasseny, director general of the African Regional Committee for the Study of the Chuche Idea, and Edmond Jouve, president of the Council of the European Society for the Study of the Chuche Idea. Comrade Kim Chong-il in his reply messages expressed thanks to them for their warm congratulations and best wishes. He in the reply messages expressed the conviction that the friendly and cooperative relations between the Workers' Party of Korea and those parties would grow stronger and develop and wished them success in their work.
